lyrics:
[Verse]
In the heart of the wild, where legends are born
Rode a lonesome cowboy, with a hat well-worn
His six-shooter gleaming, on a trusty horse he'd mount
He'd ride into the sunset, with no fear to count

[Chorus]
Yippee-yi-yay, yippee-yi-yo
Riding through the prairies where the wild winds blow
Yippee-yi-yay, yippee-yi-hey
Together they'd conquer, with no time to delay
